add:
add(obj: GameObject) → {undefined}

Add the object to the scene. Only objects added to the scene will appear.
add_keyboard_listener:
add_keyboard_listener(key: undefined, event: string, callback: Function) → {GameObject}

Attach a listener to the object. The callback will be executed when the event is emitted. Mutate the object.

For all available events, see: https://photonstorm.github.io/phaser3-docs/Phaser.Input.Events.html

For list of keycodes, see: https://github.com/photonstorm/phaser/blob/v3.22.0/src/input/keyboard/keys/KeyCodes.js
add_listener:
add_listener(obj: GameObject, event: string, callback: Function) → {undefined}

Attach a listener to the object. The callback will be executed when the event is emitted. Mutate the object.

For all available events, see: https://photonstorm.github.io/phaser3-docs/Phaser.Input.Events.html
add_to_container:
add_to_container(container: GameObject, obj: GameObject) → {undefined}

Add the given game object to the container. Mutates the container.
add_tween:
add_tween(obj: GameObject, config: ObjectConfig) → {Promise}

Creates a tween to the object and plays it. Mutate the object.
create_anim:
create_anim(anim_config: ObjectConfig) → {boolean}

Create a new animation and add it to the available animations. Animations are global i.e. once created, it can be used anytime, anywhere.

NOTE: Anims DO NOT need to be added into the scene to be used. It is automatically added to the scene when it is created.

Will return true if the animation key is valid (key is specified within the anim_config); false if the key is already in use.
create_anim_config:
create_anim_config(anims_key: string, anim_frames: undefined, frame_rate: number, duration: any, repeat: number, yoyo: boolean, show_on_start: boolean, hide_on_complete: boolean) → {ObjectConfig}

Create anims config, can be used to configure anims

For more details about the config object, see: https://photonstorm.github.io/phaser3-docs/Phaser.Types.Animations.html#.Animation
create_anim_frame_config:
create_anim_frame_config(key: string, duration: number, visible: boolean) → {ObjectConfig}

Create animation frame config, can be used to configure a specific frame within an animation.

The key should refer to an image that is already loaded. To make frame_config from spritesheet based on its frames, use create_anim_spritesheet_frame_configs instead.
create_anim_spritesheet_frame_configs:
create_anim_spritesheet_frame_configs(key: string) → {undefined}

Create list of animation frame config, can be used directly as part of anim_config's
create_award:
create_award(x: number, y: number, award_key: string) → {GameObject}

Create an award using the key associated with the award. The award key can be obtained from the Awards Hall or Awards menu, after attaining the award.

Valid award will have an on-hover VERIFIED tag to distinguish it from images created by create_image.

If student does not possess the award, this function will return a untagged, default image.
create_config:
create_config(lst: List) → {ObjectConfig}

Transforms the given list into an object config. The list follows the format of list([key1, value1], [key2, value2]).

e.g list(["alpha", 0], ["duration", 1000])
create_container:
create_container(x: number, y: number) → {GameObject}

Create a container object. Container is able to contain any other game object, and the positions of contained game object will be relative to the container.

Rendering the container as visible or invisible will also affect the contained game object.

Container can also contain another container.

0, 0 is located at the top, left hand side.

For more details about container object, see: https://photonstorm.github.io/phaser3-docs/Phaser.GameObjects.Container.html
create_ellipse:
create_ellipse(x: number, y: number, width: number, height: number, fill: number, alpha: number) → {GameObject}

Create an ellipse object.
create_image:
create_image(x: number, y: number, asset_key: string) → {undefined}

Create an image using the key associated with a loaded image. If key is not associated with any loaded image, throws error.

0, 0 is located at the top, left hand side.
create_interactive_config:
create_interactive_config(draggable: boolean, use_hand_cursor: boolean, pixel_perfect: boolean, alpha_tolerance: number) → {ObjectConfig}

Create interactive config object, can be used to configure interactive settings.

For more details about interactive config object, see: https://photonstorm.github.io/phaser3-docs/Phaser.Types.Input.html#.InputConfiguration
create_rect:
create_rect(x: number, y: number, width: number, height: number, fill: number, alpha: number) → {GameObject}

Create a rectangle object.

0, 0 is located at the top, left hand side.
create_sound_config:
create_sound_config(mute: boolean, volume: number, rate: number, detune: number, seek: number, loop: boolean, delay: number) → {ObjectConfig}

Create sound config object, can be used to configure sound settings.

For more details about sound config object, see: https://photonstorm.github.io/phaser3-docs/Phaser.Types.Sound.html#.SoundConfig
create_spritesheet_config:
create_spritesheet_config(frame_width: number, frame_height: number, start_frame: number, margin: number, spacing: number) → {ObjectConfig}

Create spritesheet config, can be used to configure the frames within the spritesheet. Can be used as config at load_spritesheet.
create_text:
create_text(x: number, y: number, text: string, config: ObjectConfig) → {GameObject}

Create a text object.

0, 0 is located at the top, left hand side.
create_text_config:
create_text_config(font_family: string, font_size: string, color: string, stroke: string, stroke_thickness: number, align: string) → {ObjectConfig}

Create text config object, can be used to stylise text object.

font_family: for available font_family, see: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-family#Valid_family_names

align: must be either 'left', 'right', 'center', or 'justify'

For more details about text config, see: https://photonstorm.github.io/phaser3-docs/Phaser.Types.GameObjects.Text.html#.TextStyle
create_tween_config:
create_tween_config(target_prop: string, target_value: undefined, delay: number, duration: number, ease: undefined, on_complete: Function, yoyo: boolean, loop: number, loop_delay: number, on_loop: Function) → {ObjectConfig}

Create tween config object, can be used to configure tween settings.

For more details about tween config object, see: https://photonstorm.github.io/phaser3-docs/Phaser.Types.Tweens.html#.TweenBuilderConfig
destroy_obj:
destroy_obj(obj: GameObject) → {void}

Destroy the given game object. Destroyed game object is removed from the scene, and all of its listeners is also removed.
get_screen_display_height:
get_screen_display_height() → {number}

Get game screen display height (accounting window size).
get_screen_display_width:
get_screen_display_width() → {number}

Get game screen display width (accounting window size).
load_image:
load_image(key: string, url: string) → {void}

Load the image asset into the scene for use. All images must be loaded before used in create_image.
load_sound:
load_sound(key: string, url: string) → {void}

Load the sound asset into the scene for use. All sound must be loaded before used in play_sound.
load_spritesheet:
load_spritesheet(key: string, url: string, spritesheet_config: ObjectConfig) → {undefined}

Load the spritesheet into the scene for use. All spritesheet must be loaded before used in create_image.
play_anim_on_image:
play_anim_on_image(image: GameObject, anims_key: string) → {undefined}

Start playing the given animation on image game object.
play_sound:
play_sound(key: string, config: ObjectConfig) → {void}

Play the sound associated with the key. Throws error if key is non-existent.
prepend_remote_url:
prepend_remote_url(asset_key: string) → {string}

Prepend the given asset key with the remote path (S3 path).
set_alpha:
set_alpha(obj: GameObject, alpha: number) → {undefined}

Set the alpha of the object. Mutate the object.
set_display_size:
set_display_size(obj: GameObject, x: number, y: number) → {undefined}

Set the display size of the object. Mutate the object.
set_flip:
set_flip(obj: GameObject, x: boolean, y: boolean) → {undefined}

Sets the horizontal and flipped state of the object. Mutate the object.
set_interactive:
set_interactive(obj: GameObject, config: ObjectConfig) → {undefined}

Set the interactivity of the object. Mutate the object.

Rectangle and Ellipse are not able to receive configs, only boolean i.e. set_interactive(rect, true); set_interactive(ellipse, false)
set_origin:
set_origin(obj: GameObject, x: number, y: number) → {undefined}

Set the origin in which all position related will be relative to. In other words, the anchor of the object. Mutate the object.
set_position:
set_position(obj: GameObject, x: number, y: number) → {undefined}

Set the position of the game object Mutate the object
set_rotation:
set_rotation(obj: GameObject, rad: number) → {undefined}

Set the rotation of the object. Mutate the object.
set_scale:
set_scale(obj: GameObject, x: number, y: number) → {undefined}

Set the scale of the object. Mutate the object.
